  "commentary": "With SPX at 7028.33 sitting between the max negative gamma at 7015 and max positive gamma at 7050, dealers are caught in a narrow hedging band where they'll buy any dips toward 7015 and sell any push toward the massive 7050 gamma wall. The PIN regime with 108B in total GEX creates strong mean-reverting forces, and the recent wall_break event suggests we just tested key support/resistance that dealers will now defend more aggressively. Watch 7015 as the critical support where dealer buying should kick in hard, while 7050 represents the ceiling where dealer selling pressure intensifies.\n\nBottom line: expect tight range-bound action between 7015-7050 with dealers capping both sides.",
